# Legacy UI migration rules

Apply only when explicitly performing the legacy UI migration in the scoped frontend files.

- Preserve existing copy, labels, and text unless the requested component migration requires a status mapping.
- Keep changes to leaf-level UI primitives within the existing page and shell structure.
- Do not replace the existing routing, page header, or application shell as part of a primitive migration.
- Keep diffs scoped; do not reformat untouched files or run broad fixers.
